  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WASH assistance for vulnerable households and communities to prevent and mitigate COVID-19 transmission</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">After more than nine years of conflict across the country, Syria is particularly vulnerable to a large-scale COVID-19 outbreak. This project will provide life-saving WASH support to people vulnerable to COVID-19 transmission in Aleppo, Hama, Idleb and Rural Damascus in coordination with other actors. DRC will flexibly intervene where most needed, including where DRC is strategically positioned for access in comparison to other responders. DRC is already working in Aleppo, Hama, and Rural Damascus governorates and will use this action to scale-up assistance, ensuring a comprehensive response to the population in need, including the 7,750 beneficiaries targeted under this action. Coordination with other actors will maximize response efficiency. With access to Aleppo, Hama and Rural Damascus facilitated through SARC and relevant technical line ministries, DRC stands ready to begin activities for this project as soon as it is funded. DRC is coordinating with SARC and local authorities to gain access to Idleb and have received positive feedback that this will be facilitated in a timely manner.


The immediate basic needs on the ground for affected populations, as reported through the WASH sector include access to safe and sufficient water and hygiene items to practice proper hygiene practices in order to help prevent human-to-human transmission. The targeted beneficiary populations are living in communities with little or no existing WASH infrastructure in place. Hygiene kits, water, and water tanks will be distributed in target locations to slow, suppress and stop the spread of COVID-19.


The project accords with the WASH sector&#x2019;s COVID-19 strategy of providing assistance to ensure good and consistently applied WASH practices in communities. It will together with the interventions of other actors create a safe environment for other humanitarian activities in the sectors of education, protection, and livelihoods to be delivered. Project locations will remain flexible to enable DRC to respond to the most critical needs expected locations are vulnerable communities within Aleppo, Hama, Idleb and Rural Damascus, however DRC maintains the flexibility to prioritize activities in certain locations based on need meaning not all activities will necessarily be implemented in all selected locations.
 
In order to reduce, mitigate and address COVID-19 risk factors, DRC proposes a comprehensive WASH program which will work to expand access to vital water and hygiene assistance to highly vulnerable and underserved populations that are particularly vulnerable to COVID-19 transmission. Interventions will include hygiene kit distribution in communities and water trucking including water tank provision when needed.</narrative>
  </description>
